Export a dataset to the warehouse with schema logging

Source: R/export_with_schema_warehouse.R
export_with_schema_warehouse.Rd

Safely exports a dataset to the warehouse-ready location and logs its schema metadata to a warehouse-specific SQL schema log. This function wraps both `safe_fwrite_warehouse()` and `sql_schema_log_warehouse()` to ensure standardized output and metadata tracking for the data warehouse pipeline.

Usage

export_with_schema_warehouse(
  data,
  path = NULL,
  table_name,
  data_year,
  data_source,
  data_description,
  dim_description = NULL,
  user_note,
  char_cols = c("cds", "county_code", "district_code", "school_code"),
  compress = FALSE,
  n_check = 6,
  export_log_path = "T:/Data Warehouse/Warehouse Ready Files/export_log.csv",
  max_char = 255,
  primary_key = NULL,
  foreign_keys = NULL,
  canonical_table_id = NULL,
  dimension_type = NULL
)

Arguments

data

A data frame to be exported and documented.

path

Optional. The file path where the data will be saved. If `NULL`, the path is generated internally.

table_name

A valid SQL-style name for the exported table.

data_year

A 4-digit string or number indicating the year of the data.

data_source

A short string describing the source of the data (e.g., `"CDE"`, `"SBAC"`).

data_description

A human-readable description of the dataset being exported.

dim_description

Optional. A short description for dimension tables (if applicable).

user_note

A brief note about the export (e.g., filtering, transformations, versioning).

char_cols

Character vector of column names to force as character during export. Defaults to common CDE identifiers.

compress

Logical. If `TRUE`, exports the file as `.csv.gz`. Default is `FALSE`.

n_check

Integer. Number of rows to print during export preview. Default is 6.

export_log_path

File path to the export log CSV. Default is the warehouse export log on the T drive.

max_char

Maximum allowed character length for string columns in the schema log. Default is 255.

primary_key

Optional. A vector of column names representing the table's primary key.

foreign_keys

Optional. A named list representing foreign key relationships.

canonical_table_id

Optional. A unique identifier used for linking across data products.

dimension_type

Optional. A label to describe the type of dimension (e.g., `"student"`, `"school"`).

Value

Invisibly returns `NULL`. Files are written to disk and schema is logged to the warehouse schema log.
